She said they are working with the United Nations.Speaking in Mombasa on Tuesday, Njeri said women will also play a significant role to curb violence before and after the general election.Violent attacks, some associated with terrorists, have been common during electioneering period. This aims to instil fear among the electorate. Women and youths have often been used by politicians to heckle their rivals. In Mombasa, governor aspirants' supporters have clashed publicly during national events.Njeri said NCIC has started a programme to engage women countrywide to foster peace before,during and after the August 8 polls."These politicians and supporters come home to a woman at the end of the day. It is up to women to advise and counsel them," she said.